OL,4,Cpart of UK's asylum reforms
OL,6,FThe Home Office believes its
OL,7,Fdefinition has expanded beyond what
OL,8,Fshould be considered reasonable,
OL,9,Fciting cases where serious criminals
OL,10,Fhave remained in the UK after claims
OL,11,Ftheir healthcare needs could not be
OL,12,Fmet in their homeland.
OL,14,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer said:
OL,15,F"Britain has always been a fair,
OL,16,Ftolerant and compassionate country `
OL,17,Fand this government will always defend
OL,18,Fthose values.
